project.name: Week 4 Project: Mood Ring
project.notes: The title of this piece is "Mood Ring". When I went into this I know I could just throw down a bunch of random lines but I wanted to try something unique with the programming. I've been playing this game called OMORI recently and it got me thinking a lot about depression and mental health and stuff. So I came up with an idea of a Pollock-inspired piece that sort of acted like a random reflection of an emotional state. The first palette kind of reminds me of a farmer's market with all the reds, greens, yellows, and oranges. The second palette is much more muted, with lots of blues, purples, and maybe some pinks. The first palette represents days when you're full of energy and ready to take on the world, but the second palette is when you're feeling mellow and just want to coast. If you hit the button, it's like a mood ring: how are you feeling today?
